	<td bgcolor='#FBFBFB' valign='top' width='100%' bordercolor='#FBFBFB'>
	<table width='100%' border='0' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='3'><tr><td><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><img src="http://www.eqinterface.com/images/sections/directx.gif" align="right"><br />
<br />
From the <a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/community/dev_view.jsp?id=60476" target="_blank"><b>Dev Corner</b></a><br />
<br />
<br />
<table border="0" align="center" width="90%" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="1"><tr><td><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><b>DirectX 9 on Test:</b></font></td></tr><tr><td style="BORDER: #D2D4D5 1px solid; FONT-SIZE: 11px; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana,Arial; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #E8E8E8;">In order to continue to move EverQuest forward and embrace rapidly changing graphics technology, we are going to require the use of DirectX 9 on the Test server.  DirectX 9 will better use EverQuest's graphic resources, while providing better security and performance for your computers.  You can download DirectX 9 at <a href="http://www.microsoft.com/directx" target="_blank">www.microsoft.com/directx</a>.<br />
<br />
Thanks for all of your continued help in testing EverQuest.<br />
<br />
Brenlo the Test Subject</td></tr></table><br />
<br />
---------------------<br />
<br />
