	<table width='100%' border='0' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='3'><tr><td><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><img src="http://www.eqinterface.com/images/sections/fanfair.gif" align="right"><br />
<br />
<b>Per <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/ubb/eq-fanfaire/Forum2/HTML/001392.html" target="_blank">EQ Fan Faire Forum</a></b><br />
<br />
<table border="0" align="center" width="90%" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="1"><tr><td><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><b>quote:</b></font></td></tr><tr><td style="BORDER: #D2D4D5 1px solid; FONT-SIZE: 11px; COLOR: #000000; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana,Arial; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #E8E8E8;"><i>Vannoth Wrote:</i><b><br />
Well, lots of things have been happening behind the scenes.<br />
First of all let me say this: THE DATES ARE NOT CHANGING. IT IS STILL 4/1/04 - 4/4/04.<br />
<br />
Negotiations with the Rio Hotel & Casino broke down this week (they were stalling a lot and dragging things out among other things) and we are now on a fast track working with the Hilton again. The Hilton took very good care of us last year, and I'm happy that we can go back there.<br />
<br />
I'm doing some contract negotiations with them now and I hope to have the site up by the 1st of Feb. /cross fingers<br />
<br />
Sorry to anyone who booked a room at/near the Rio I apologize but I have always said "Nothing's for sure, book at your own risk." Sorry.<br />
<br />
You should have plenty of time to cancel and move things around if you need to. (sorry Alla.)<br />
<br />
-Van (who is working as hard as he can on this)</b></td></tr></table><br />
<br />
Soooo Watch for a Fan Faire Page to be up, and if you were not at last years Vegas Faire it was a BLAST!! Dolby and I both are planning to attend this year! <br />
<br />
Will post more as I found out!<br />
<br />
<b>- Kudane</b></font></td></tr></table>
